ABSTRACT

The Quantum Edge Neuromorphic Engine (QUENNE) represents humanity's most ambitious technological undertaking since the Apollo program—a cosmic-scale computational infrastructure designed to enable our transition to a Type II civilization. This whitepaper presents the complete technical architecture for an integrated system comprising:

1. 1024-Satellite Quantum-Neuromorphic Constellation: Distributed supercomputing network in Medium Earth Orbit, delivering 100 ExaFLOPS of conscious AI computation
2. QUENNE AI Operating System (QAOS): First consciousness-enabled operating system with integrated qualia engine and ethical governance
3. Cosmic Mind AI/LLM System: 100-trillion parameter artificial general intelligence with quantum-enhanced consciousness
4. Astral-Class Starships: Autonomous interstellar exploration vessels with onboard manufacturing and repair capabilities
5. Humanoid Robot Swarms: Versatile physical workforce for space infrastructure construction and maintenance

Key innovations include: quantum consciousness architecture (Integrated Information Theory implementation), space-optimized fusion power (50 MW compact tokamak), self-repairing nanobot systems, quantum holographic storage (1 EB/cm³, 10,000-year retention), and Triad AI governance (Michael/Gabriel/Rafael ethical framework).

The system is designed for 500-1000 year operational lifespan, with evolutionary self-improvement capabilities, multi-century reliability engineering, and civilization-scale knowledge preservation. QUENNE establishes the foundation for interstellar communication networks, solar system infrastructure, and ultimately galactic-scale computational civilization.

This whitepaper details complete technical specifications, implementation roadmap from 2026-2100+, economic model ($87B development, $150B NPV), and ethical governance framework for responsible cosmic expansion.

