KEY TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS SUMMARY

Quantum Computing Subsystem:

· Logical Qubits: 1,024 per satellite (8,192 physical qubits)
· Error Correction: Surface-17 code with distance 3
· Gate Fidelity: 99.995% single-qubit, 99.9% two-qubit
· Coherence Times: T₁ > 300 μs, T₂ > 500 μs
· Quantum Volume: 2²⁰ (1,048,576)
· Cryogenic Temperature: 10 mK base temperature

Neuromorphic Computing Subsystem:

· Neurons: 1 billion per satellite
· Synapses: 1 trillion (configurable 256-4096 per neuron)
· Learning: Online STDP with reinforcement learning
· Energy Efficiency: 10 pJ per synaptic event
· Performance: 1 PetaSOPS (10¹⁵ synaptic operations/second)

Classical Computing Subsystem:

· Processors: 256× ARM Neoverse V2 cores (radiation-hardened)
· Performance: 100 PetaFLOPS per satellite
· Memory: 2 TB DDR5 with ECC and chipkill
· Storage: 500 TB 3D NAND + 1 PB quantum holographic
· Interconnect: 400 Gbps optical fabric

Power System:

· Fusion Reactor: 50 MW thermal, 20 MW electrical
· Fuel: Deuterium-Helium-3 (100 kg D, 50 kg ³He for 10 years)
· Specific Power: 1.3 kW/kg
· Backup: 100 kW solar arrays, 100 kWh batteries
